'''Kabutozuka Kofun''' (兜塚古墳) is a {{ill|kofun|ja|古墳|1=Kofun|12=draft|12=draft}} from the late {{ill|Kofun period|ja|古墳時代|12=draft|12=draft}} located in {{ill|Tsurumi-ku, Yokohama|ja|鶴見区|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Yokohama|ja|横浜市|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Kanagawa Prefecture|ja|神奈川県|12=draft|12=draft}}. It is a {{ill|circular tumulus (empun)|ja|円墳|1=Round Kofun|1=Round Kofun|12=draft|12=draft}}, though its mound has been significantly damaged and flattened. It is believed to have been part of the '''Kajiyama Kofun Group'''. Although it was constructed in the {{ill|6th century|ja|6世紀|12=draft|12=draft}}, there is a legend associated with the {{ill|15th-century|ja|15世紀|12=draft|12=draft}} military commander {{ill|Ōta Dōkan|ja|太田道灌|12=draft|12=draft}}.

== Location and Overview ==

In the northwestern part of Tsurumi Ward, on the northern edge of the {{ill|Shimosueyoshi Plateau|ja|下末吉台地|12=draft|12=draft}} (40–50 meters above sea level) facing the south bank of the {{ill|Tsurumi River|ja|鶴見川|12=draft|12=draft}}, multiple {{ill|kofun groups|ja|古墳群|12=draft|12=draft}} and {{ill|yokoana tomb groups|ja|横穴墓群|1=Cave tomb|lt=Cave tombs|12=draft|12=draft}} were once distributed.

