{{coord|35|32|03.8|N|139|39|42.7|E|region:JP-14|display=title}}{{Location map|Japan Kanagawa Prefecture| label =Kabutozuka Kofun| position = bottom| mark = Red pog.svg| marksize = 10|relief = 1| width = 250| caption={{Left|Location Map}}}}

'''Kabutozuka Kofun''' (兜塚古墳) is a [[:en:Kofun|Kofun]] from the late [[:en:Kofun period|Kofun period]] located in {{ill|Tsurumi-ku, Yokohama|ja|鶴見区|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tsurumi-ku, Yokohama|qq=}}, [[:en:Yokohama|Yokohama]], [[:en:Kanagawa Prefecture|Kanagawa Prefecture]]. It is a {{ill|circular tumulus (empun)|ja|円墳|1=Round Kofun|1=Round Kofun|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/circular tumulus (empun)|13=User:Immanuelle/Round Kofun|qq=}}, though its mound has been significantly damaged and flattened. It is believed to have been part of the '''Kajiyama Kofun Group'''. Although it was constructed in the [[:en:6th century|6th century]], there is a legend associated with the [[:en:15th century|15th-century]] military commander [[:en:Ōta Dōkan|Ōta Dōkan]].

== Location and Overview ==

In the northwestern part of Tsurumi Ward, on the northern edge of the {{ill|Shimosueyoshi Plateau|ja|下末吉台地|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shimosueyoshi Plateau|qq=}} (40–50 meters above sea level) facing the south bank of the [[:en:Tsurumi River|Tsurumi River]], multiple {{ill|kofun groups|ja|古墳群|1=Kofun cluster|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/kofun groups|13=User:Immanuelle/Kofun cluster|qq=}} and {{ill|yokoana tomb groups|ja|横穴墓群|1=Cave tomb|lt=Cave tombs|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/yokoana tomb groups|13=User:Immanuelle/Cave tomb|qq=}} were once distributed.

The cluster of kofun concentrated in {{ill|Komaoka, Yokohama|ja|駒岡|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Komaoka, Yokohama|qq=}} is known as the '''Komaoka Kofun Group''', which includes the {{ill|Komaoka Hyōtan-yama Kofun|ja|駒岡瓢箪山古墳|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Komaoka Hyōtan-yama Kofun|qq=}}, {{ill|Komaoka Dō-no-mae Kofun|ja|駒岡堂の前古墳|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Komaoka Dō-no-mae Kofun|qq=}}, and {{ill|Iwaseyama Cave Tomb Group|ja|岩瀬山横穴墓群|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Iwaseyama Cave Tomb Group|qq=}}. 

Kabutozuka Kofun is located on a ridge to the east of the hills where the Komaoka Kofun Group is situated, at the northern end of the ridge. It is said that there were other kofun besides Kabutozuka in the area, collectively referred to as the '''Kajiyama Kofun Group'''. 

== Legend of Ōta Dōkan ==

In the [[:en:15th century|15th century]], [[:en:Ōta Dōkan|Ōta Dōkan]] was searching for a suitable hill to build a satellite castle for [[:en:Edo Castle|Edo Castle]]. He found the {{ill|Kase Plateau|ja|加瀬台|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kase Plateau|qq=}} (Kaseyama) in present-day [[:en:Kawasaki, Kanagawa|Kawasaki, Kanagawa]] and spent the night there. During his sleep, he dreamt of a [[:en:Egret|white heron]] flying away with his helmet (kabuto) and dropping it after a while. Upon waking, Dōkan took this as an ill omen and abandoned his plans to build the castle on Kase Plateau. Since then, the plateau has been known as "Yumemigasaki" (Dream-Viewing Hill), and the spot where his helmet fell came to be called "Kabutozuka" (Helmet Mound), which corresponds to the current site of Kabutozuka Kofun.

Although unrelated to this legend, the Kase Plateau in Kawasaki, where Dōkan abandoned his construction plans, contains the {{ill|Kasedai Kofun Group|ja|加瀬台古墳群|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kasedai Kofun Group|qq=}} (also known as the Yumemigasaki Kofun Group).

